Amid the criticisms that have greeted his choice of running mate, the presidential candidate of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu has revealed why he must win the 2023 presidential election. The former Lagos State Governor who spoke on Wednesday while unveiling Senator Kashim Shettima as his running mate asserted that he will have to win the presidential election because he needs to create jobs for Nigerians. According to him, his victory in the forthcoming election would eliminate religious and ethnic division among Nigerians while harping on the need for all to be united. He also assured that his victory would bring about quality education for Nigerians and the elimination of poverty. “We must win this election so that we can bring jobs, eliminate poverty, educate our children, and bring up our grandchildren without thinking of religious division or ethnic division. “We are one, our passport is one; greenback is one. one nation, one destiny,” he said.